    </did>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_e86a62231496d9960a05459fbae3dc9a">
      <head>Content Description</head>
      <p>Collection consists of individual postcards and photographs of İzmir (Smyrna), dating from
        the late 1800s through the 1950s. Some postcards are blank; others have been mailed and
        contain correspondence most often in French, Greek, or Ottoman-Turkish. Images depicted vary
        but include markets, mosques, streets and houses, harbor scenes, piers, the clock tower. A
        subset of images depicts the Great Fire of 1922 from the Greco-Turkish War, Greek refugees
        fleeing by boat, and a floating corpse. There are images of both people and methods of
        transportation.</p>
    </scopecontent>
